@model NxT.Mvc.Models.GitHubUser

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "About";
}
<h1>About this project</h1>

<div class="d-flex justify-content-center">
    <div class="card w-50 mt-3 mb-3 rounded" style="min-width: 450px;">
        <h3 class="card-header d-flex justify-content-center">Author</h3>
        <div class="card-body">
            <div class="d-flex align-items-center justify-content-around">
                <img class="img-thumbnail mb-3 rounded-circle"
                     src="@Model.AvatarUrl"
                     alt="Github Avatar"
                     style="width: 120px;" />

                <h4 class="card-title">@Model.Name - @Model.Login</h4>
            </div>
            <p class="card-text">@Model.Bio</p>
        </div>
        <div class="card-footer d-flex justify-content-center">
            <a class="btn btn-outline-primary rounded" href="@Model.HtmlUrl">My GitHub</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

<h3>Speaking a bit about the project</h3>
<p class="text-body-primary text-black fs-4">
    This project is based on another project with the same name (<a href="https://github.com/acenelio/workshop-asp-net-core-mvc">SalesWebMvc</a>) by Professor <a href="https://github.com/acenelio">Nélio Alves</a>,
    which was done in the <a href="https://www.udemy.com/course/programacao-orientada-a-objetos-csharp">C# course</a> on <i>Udemy.</i>
</p>
<p class="text-body-primary text-black fs-4">
    My first challenge with this project was deciding between using .NET 2.1 (which is the course version) or attempting to update this project to .NET Core 8.0.
    And that's exactly what I did: I challenged myself to update the project, which took more time, since a lot has changed in the 6 years since .NET Core 2.
</p>
<p class="text-body-primary text-black fs-4">
    So, to see all the changes that have been implemented and what has changed in <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/overview">ASP.NET</a> and <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet">.NET</a> during this period,
    just check my GitHub (and don't forget to check the original project):
</p>
<p class="text-info-emphasis">
    <i>Feel free to contribute or comment on anything :D</i>
</p>
